  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Haven't looked into why this happens but when I've noticed when testing communities with multiple members, sometimes a member of the community looses their display name and renders their 3 word password instead:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-10-24 11-27-52](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/197494931-48cfaa33-893c-48df-a16a-933e9fe7a3f9.png)\r\n\r\nSometimes, this happens after a, say, second member has joined the community.\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce (not 100% reliable, as this doesn't always happen):\r\n\r\n1. Create desktop instance, use account A to create community\r\n2. Run second desktop instance, use account B\r\n3. Invite account B to the community via account A\r\n4. Join/request access from account B\r\n5. Log out of account B and create account C on second desktop instance\r\n6. Repeat 3) with account C instead of B\r\n7. Repeat 4)\r\n\r\nThen at some point, a member might loose their display name. In the case of the screenshot, the first member no longer shows their display name",
